    <!-- OVERVIEW SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="overview" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. Overview</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>DBSchemaManager</strong> is a Catalyst Model that provides comprehensive database schema management capabilities. It handles schema initialization, table listing, and schema comparison across multiple database types (ENCY, Forager).</p>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Key Responsibilities</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Manage schema creation from <strong>DBIx::Class Result classes</strong> (not raw SQL files)</li>
                <li>List and discover tables in connected databases</li>
                <li>Manage schema initialization at application startup</li>
                <li>Support multiple database connections</li>
                <li>Provide schema introspection and comparison capabilities</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="info-box" style="background: var(--nav-bg); border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 0;"><strong>🔑 Core Philosophy:</strong> DBSchemaManager works exclusively with <strong>DBIx::Class Result classes</strong> (files in <code>lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/</code>), not raw SQL files. This approach provides:</p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: 0;">
                    <li>Type safety through Perl class definitions</li>
                    <li>Version control of schema changes in source code</li>
                    <li>Relationships defined in code, not just foreign keys</li>
                    <li>Helper methods for common operations</li>
                    <li>Easy integration with Catalyst ORM layer</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="warning-box" style="background: var(--nav-bg); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 0;"><strong>⚠️ Documentation Status:</strong> The <strong>DBEncy</strong> and <strong>DBForager</strong> models referenced in this guide do not yet have dedicated documentation files. See <a href="/Documentation/Models" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">Models Documentation</a> for model index. Each Result class in <code>lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/</code> should follow patterns documented in <a href="/Documentation/Result_Class_Development_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">Result Class Development Guide</a>.</p>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

